</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Dependency</p></t=
d>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Clarification is =
needed for the below:</p>
<ol>
<li><p><strong>OD Limits Setup</strong>:<br>
 No current requirement to set up overdraft limits or rates in 10x, but cla=
rification is needed on whether any such data will be received.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Account Lifecycle Dates</strong>:<br>
 Opening/closing dates in 10x will reflect the<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>mi=
rroring timestamp</strong>, not the actual account dates. The approach is s=
till being defined with architects.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Balance Updates</strong>:<br>
 PO expects<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>near real-time (&lt;3s)</strong><span=
>&nbsp;</span>updates from trading bank, but the<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>=
source and feasibility of intraday data</strong><span>&nbsp;</span>are stil=
l under architectural review.</p></li>
<li><p><strong>Transaction Synchronisation</strong>:<br>
 Trading bank operates as a<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>batch system</strong>=
, sending daily transaction files post-processing. Architects are still det=
ermining<span>&nbsp;</span><strong>timing and handling of intraday vs. end-=
of-day data</strong>.</p></li>
</ol><p><br><strong>Dependency:</strong></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>ACD to be signed off or concrete solution is confirmed by the Account t=
eam.&nbsp;</li>
</ul></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">#4 is just impacting=
 the user experience but not to the overall solution design.&nbsp;</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<div class=3D"content-wrapper">
<p><time datetime=3D"2025-08-22" class=3D"date-past">22 Aug 2025</time>&nbs=
p;</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
