<h3 id=3D"id-10.SD:TradingBankAccountMirroring-Non-FunctionalRequirementsTr=
aceability">Non-Functional Requirements Traceability</h3>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation"><span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluen=
ce-information-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p>Noted that the below requirements belong to the Account hosting system /=
 Ledger and it's not end-to-end from Channel perspective.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>The following NFRs have been defined in the requirements:&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Data Retention:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong style=3D"text-align: left;">25-months of historical data to be =
loaded for mirrored trading bank accounts.&nbsp;</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong style=3D"text-align: left;">Performance:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><strong style=3D"text-align: left;">The system will automatically trans=
fer and load historical transactions and balances to the account host platf=
orm<span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>within 30 secon=
ds once the</span></strong> Trading Bank mirrored account has been activate=
d on the account host platform.&nbsp;</li>
<li><p style=3D"text-align: left;"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">A tra=
nsaction has been processed<span>&nbsp;</span>against the Trading Bank mirr=
ored accounts, </span><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);">the transaction (i=
ncluding narratives) and balance will be transferred and processed into the=
 account host platform <strong>within 3 seconds.</strong></span></p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-10.SD:TradingBankAccountMirroring-TechnicalDebt">Technical Deb=
t</h2>
<p></p>
<p>N/A</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-10.SD:TradingBankAccountMirroring-Solution"><span>Solution</sp=
an></h1>
<h2 id=3D"id-10.SD:TradingBankAccountMirroring-SolutionOverview"><span>Solu=
tion Overview</span></h2>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><p style=3D"text-align: left;"><strong>Accounts list</strong> - no chan=
ge as account list still expected to come from 10x.</p></li>
<li>Logic would be needed if Decision is to Hide&nbsp;<strong style=3D"lett=
er-spacing: 0.0px;">Account activity - Interest and tax</strong>&nbsp;Tab f=
or trading bank account.=20
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Either to hide by product type or account number. (6 digits)</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Potential logic to hide/show overdraft limit in<strong> Account activit=
y - Account details</strong> depending on products type.</li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"80fc5052-708f-444f-a8=
d4-70d99a9b19fa">For </span><strong style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;"><span =
class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"80fc5052-708f-444f-a8d4-70d99a9=
b19fa">Statements - Account statements,&nbsp;</span></strong><span class=3D=
"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"80fc5052-708f-444f-a8d4-70d99a9b19fa">a=
ction is needed to confirm with Architect if the same ECM API is used to ge=
t the statement list and statement. (If not, separate logic is required to =
handle Trading Bank statement and 10x statement nicely in EXP/CAP API layer=
)</span></li>
<li>logic to hide <strong style=3D"letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Statements - Ann=
ual interest summary </strong>for trading bank account.</li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"e7eee213-adcd-4655-87=
1e-096345e261f2">Payment / Transfer needs to confirm if users can make paym=
ent in COL / W1C and which one is going to be the golden source.</span>&nbs=
p;=20
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Are they supposed to make and approve payment in two different sources?=
 and how do the data get synchronised?&nbsp;</li>
<li>It will be pending on transaction synchronisation solution too.&nbsp;</=
li>
</ul></li>
<li><p style=3D"text-align: left;"><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-ma=
rker" data-ref=3D"601722f2-7319-471e-80ca-8113e4cdaa69">Transaction details=
 -&nbsp;</span></strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"6=
01722f2-7319-471e-80ca-8113e4cdaa69">less fields are displayed for Trading =
bank account. Assume if One Core Arrangement CAP API is returning less data=
 no handling is required at the UI level. Just display the field when value=
s are returned and hide the label if not presented.</span>&nbsp;</p></li>
<li><strong>Transaction list - </strong>continue to source from ATLAS and n=
o changes are expected.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
